The paper deals with LDPC codes and their LP decoding thresholds, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses graph properties and their impact on the LP decoding thresholds, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of redundant checks and their impact on the LP decoding thresholds is a topic related to coding theory and error correction (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the geometric interpretation of pseudocodewords, which is a topic related to signal processing and image processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the rigidity property of graphs, which is a topic related to network science and graph theory (cs.NI).
